description.plain: The song begins with him being in a sort of denial about missing his significant other. He describes “lying to himself” about all of the signs of this other person in day to day life.  The chorus describes looking for love but struggling because only this other person can fill that space. He then speaks about drinking, overthinking, and other things he shouldn’t be doing in order to again.. fill the void. He starts to accept the fact that he may never see this other person again and blames himself for ruining it. The song ends with him asking how to make this person love him.

songs.title: From The Grave

description.plain:
‘From The Grave’ is the eighth song from the Game of Thrones inspired For The Throne album. James Arthur announced the track on his Twitter account on April 16th 2019, ten days before it’s release:
https://twitter.com/JamesArthur23/status/1118191952434991104?s=20
This song appears to be about the forbidden love between Prince Rhaegar Targaryen, who was married to Elia Martell, and Lady Lyanna Stark,  who was promised to Robert Baratheon. Their union was famously the cause of Robert’s Rebellion, as the world mistakenly believed that Rhaegar had abducted Lyanna against her will when, in reality, they had been secretly married. James Arthur takes on the role of Rhaegar as he begs Lyanna to stay strong even though he’s at war miles away.
